                            <comment id="17444526" author="rfscholte" created="Tue, 16 Nov 2021 13:16:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Worth mentioning: if there&apos;s no separator nor value, then it&apos;ll represent the default value &lt;tt&gt;true&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
IIRC if there is a separator but no value, it represents an empty string.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17444976" author="mthmulders" created="Wed, 17 Nov 2021 07:20:07 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&#160;if there&apos;s no separator nor value, then it&apos;ll represent the default value &lt;tt&gt;true&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I think that is not true. With &lt;tt&gt;-Dv -Dw=x&lt;/tt&gt;, from a Commons CLI perspective, the first &lt;tt&gt;-D&lt;/tt&gt; will have one value: &lt;tt&gt;v&lt;/tt&gt;. The second &lt;tt&gt;-D&lt;/tt&gt; will have two values, &lt;tt&gt;x&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;y&lt;/tt&gt;. Inside Maven, we &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven/blob/master/maven-embedder/src/main/java/org/apache/maven/cli/MavenCli.java#L1762&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;interpret&lt;/a&gt; that as &lt;tt&gt;v=true&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;x=y&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17444989" author="rfscholte" created="Wed, 17 Nov 2021 07:55:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Confirmed, this is indeed how Maven handles the -D flags internally, but it could help with a proper solution here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17445035" author="rfscholte" created="Wed, 17 Nov 2021 09:26:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As of 1.5.0 &lt;a href=&quot;https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-cli/apidocs/org/apache/commons/cli/CommandLine.html#getOptionProperties-org.apache.commons.cli.Option-&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;CommandLine.getOptionProperties(Option option)&lt;/a&gt; should do exactly this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17445050" author="mthmulders" created="Wed, 17 Nov 2021 09:55:49 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;As of 1.5.0 &lt;a href=&quot;https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-cli/apidocs/org/apache/commons/cli/CommandLine.html#getOptionProperties-org.apache.commons.cli.Option-&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;CommandLine.getOptionProperties(Option option)&lt;/a&gt; should do exactly this.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ah, interesting, we didn&apos;t spot that one, but that would make Mavens code even cleaner. Regardless of whether we use &lt;tt&gt;getOptionProperties()&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;getOptions()&lt;/tt&gt; (&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven/pull/605/files#diff-b8b814f5b6b3855ae79dc45a0266b94871193dcef42803c316e07409e94af35c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;as we did in the PR&lt;/a&gt;) the issue reported here remains...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17756317" author="garydgregory" created="Sat, 19 Aug 2023 13:42:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mthmulders&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mthmulders&quot;&gt;mthmulders&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Are we all squared away? Can this issue be closed?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17756544" author="mthmulders" created="Sun, 20 Aug 2023 14:07:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ggregory&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ggregory&quot;&gt;ggregory&lt;/a&gt;, judging from the comments here, and from running my own tests, the issue is still present in Commons CLI. As far as the report goes, we found a way in Maven to deal with it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I leave it up to you to decide if you want to investigate further or close because we found a way to deal with it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17756547" author="garydgregory" created="Sun, 20 Aug 2023 14:30:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Poviding a failing unit test would help.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
